1
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:02,235
( Baby crying )

2
00:00:08,976 --> 00:00:10,945
Kakyoin: That piercing noise...

3
00:00:10,978 --> 00:00:12,980
( Crying continues )

4
00:00:16,316 --> 00:00:18,318
( Machinery humming )

5
00:00:22,789 --> 00:00:24,824
( Groaning )

6
00:00:26,393 --> 00:00:28,395
( Crying continues )

7
00:00:29,563 --> 00:00:30,531
Huh

8
00:00:30,564 --> 00:00:32,533
♪

9
00:00:34,768 --> 00:00:36,436
What is this place?

10
00:00:38,272 --> 00:00:40,841
An amusement park?

11
00:00:40,874 --> 00:00:43,977
I’ve never been here before.

12
00:00:44,011 --> 00:00:45,746
W-why in the world

13
00:00:45,779 --> 00:00:48,515
am I riding on a Ferris wheel
in my pajamas?

14
00:00:48,549 --> 00:00:51,218
How’d I get here?

15
00:00:51,251 --> 00:00:52,419
The desert.

16
00:00:52,452 --> 00:00:53,820
I remember being in the desert,

17
00:00:53,854 --> 00:00:56,623
riding through Saudi Arabia
on camelback.

18
00:00:56,657 --> 00:00:58,859
But where are the others?

19
00:00:58,892 --> 00:01:00,327
( Crying continues )

20
00:01:00,360 --> 00:01:01,928
Did they abandon me?

21
00:01:01,962 --> 00:01:04,565
- ( Dog whimpers )
- ( Gasps )

22
00:01:05,899 --> 00:01:06,900
( Crying baby continues )

23
00:01:06,934 --> 00:01:09,603
This isn’t making any sense.

24
00:01:09,636 --> 00:01:12,239
There’s not a soul
anywhere in the amusement park,

25
00:01:12,272 --> 00:01:14,808
so why do I hear
the cries of a baby?

26
00:01:14,842 --> 00:01:16,744
And for that matter,
where is it?

27
00:01:16,777 --> 00:01:17,945
♪

28
00:01:17,978 --> 00:01:19,546
( Gasps )

29
00:01:24,585 --> 00:01:25,986
♪

30
00:01:26,019 --> 00:01:27,020
Hmm?

31
00:01:31,658 --> 00:01:35,428
( Gasps ) Th-this card is...

32
00:01:35,462 --> 00:01:38,031
Death 13.

33
00:01:38,065 --> 00:01:39,500
( Spurting )

34
00:01:39,533 --> 00:01:41,835
Oh, no! The card is moving!

35
00:01:41,869 --> 00:01:43,838
( Card laughs )

36
00:01:45,372 --> 00:01:46,840
( Kakyoin screams )

37
00:01:56,316 --> 00:01:57,617
( Screams )

38
00:01:57,651 --> 00:02:01,588
Polnareff: Kakyoin. Kakyoin!

39
00:02:01,622 --> 00:02:03,491
Hey, take it easy.

40
00:02:03,524 --> 00:02:05,359
Stop screaming
and shaking the bed

41
00:02:05,392 --> 00:02:07,327
like that creepy girl
from "the exorcist."

42
00:02:07,361 --> 00:02:08,462
You’re weirding me out.

43
00:02:08,495 --> 00:02:09,997
Kakyoin: Where are we?

44
00:02:10,030 --> 00:02:12,332
Polnareff: Don’t ask
stupid questions.

45
00:02:12,366 --> 00:02:15,369
Now come on,
and get up already, would you?

46
00:02:16,970 --> 00:02:19,339
- ( Kakyoin groans )
- ( Birds chirping )

47
00:02:19,373 --> 00:02:22,009
Polnareff: After breakfast,
we’re gonna take to the skies.

48
00:02:22,042 --> 00:02:25,546
Looks like
another scorcher today.

49
00:02:25,579 --> 00:02:29,349
( Kakyoin sighs )
I had a terrible nightmare.

50
00:02:29,383 --> 00:02:31,952
It was truly horrifying.

51
00:02:31,985 --> 00:02:34,521
Polnareff: You don’t say?
Lay on the details.

52
00:02:34,555 --> 00:02:36,524
I wanna hear all about it.

53
00:02:36,557 --> 00:02:38,659
Kakyoin: Well, the thing is,
I can’t remember.

54
00:02:38,692 --> 00:02:40,360
- I’ve forgotten it all.
- Polnareff: Reviens?

55
00:02:40,394 --> 00:02:43,063
Kakyoin: Regardless,
it was petrifying,

56
00:02:43,096 --> 00:02:46,333
but when you woke me up,
you pulled me out of it.

57
00:02:46,366 --> 00:02:48,068
Polnareff: Wish we
could talk more about it,

58
00:02:48,101 --> 00:02:49,669
but we’ve gotta get a move on.

59
00:02:50,938 --> 00:02:51,906
Let’s go.

60
00:02:51,939 --> 00:02:53,841
Hurry up, and get ready.

61
00:02:53,874 --> 00:02:55,642
( Kakyoin sighs )

62
00:02:55,676 --> 00:02:56,677
( Gasps )

63
00:02:59,379 --> 00:03:01,381
There’s a cut on my hand.

64
00:03:02,516 --> 00:03:05,019
But how’d it get there?

65
00:03:05,052 --> 00:03:07,054
♪

66
00:03:14,394 --> 00:03:16,396
( Singing in Japanese )

67
00:03:52,599 --> 00:03:54,134
Polnareff: Jotaro
and Mr. Joestar

68
00:03:54,168 --> 00:03:56,937
are already headed to the plane,
so we’ll meet them there,

69
00:03:56,970 --> 00:03:58,538
and the way I hear it,

70
00:03:58,572 --> 00:04:00,107
we’re traveling
500 kilometers today.

71
00:04:00,140 --> 00:04:02,476
- ( Boy screams ) No!
- Both: Huh?

72
00:04:02,509 --> 00:04:04,011
Boy: This can’t be happening!

73
00:04:04,044 --> 00:04:06,146
Please, not my poor dog!

74
00:04:06,180 --> 00:04:08,582
My dog is dead!

75
00:04:09,783 --> 00:04:12,452
Who would do such a thing?!

76
00:04:12,486 --> 00:04:15,756
Kakyoin: A dog? Dog?

77
00:04:15,789 --> 00:04:17,090
I could have sworn...

78
00:04:17,124 --> 00:04:19,960
That I saw a dead dog
not too long ago.

79
00:04:19,993 --> 00:04:21,728
Polnareff:
Whoever did this is sick,

80
00:04:21,762 --> 00:04:23,998
but there’s nothing
we can do about it.

81
00:04:24,031 --> 00:04:25,766
Let’s go.

82
00:04:25,799 --> 00:04:27,534
( Boy sobbing )

83
00:04:27,568 --> 00:04:29,603
Joseph: Hey, hey, hey, hey!

84
00:04:29,636 --> 00:04:33,707
Hey, hey, hey, hey! Hold on
a dang second there, mister!

85
00:04:33,740 --> 00:04:37,611
What exactly do you mean,
you can’t sell us the plane now?

86
00:04:37,644 --> 00:04:40,046
I seem to recall you
taking my money last night

87
00:04:40,080 --> 00:04:41,915
and saying it was a done deal.

88
00:04:41,949 --> 00:04:43,451
Man: You’ll get a full refund,

89
00:04:43,483 --> 00:04:46,486
but first we need to see
to a baby with a fever.

90
00:04:46,520 --> 00:04:48,522
- It’s 39 degrees celsius.
- Joseph: Huh?

91
00:04:48,555 --> 00:04:49,890
Man: There’s no doctor
in this town,

92
00:04:49,923 --> 00:04:51,958
so we have no choice
but to take the baby

93
00:04:51,992 --> 00:04:53,627
somewhere else to get help.

94
00:04:53,660 --> 00:04:56,563
( Joseph groans )

95
00:04:56,597 --> 00:04:57,765
Okay, then, what do you say

96
00:04:57,798 --> 00:04:59,133
to us taking
that plane over there?

97
00:04:59,166 --> 00:05:01,001
Man: I’m sorry to say
that one’s broken,

98
00:05:01,034 --> 00:05:02,702
and the others are out...
- Polnareff: What’s up?

99
00:05:02,736 --> 00:05:04,571
- Some kind of argument?
- Jotaro: Yeah.

100
00:05:04,605 --> 00:05:05,573
Kakyoin: A baby?

101
00:05:05,606 --> 00:05:06,774
( Baby crying )

102
00:05:06,807 --> 00:05:09,643
- A baby.
- ( Crying continues )

103
00:05:09,676 --> 00:05:12,179
I remember
hearing a baby’s cries...

104
00:05:13,514 --> 00:05:14,782
But where?

105
00:05:14,815 --> 00:05:16,950
Man: You’ll be able
to use the plane

106
00:05:16,984 --> 00:05:18,686
after it gets back
tomorrow night.

107
00:05:18,719 --> 00:05:20,754
We can renegotiate
and talk prices then.

108
00:05:20,787 --> 00:05:22,656
Joseph: Did you say,
"tomorrow night"?

109
00:05:22,689 --> 00:05:24,824
Our group has
someone’s life on the line,

110
00:05:24,858 --> 00:05:25,992
just like you guys do.

111
00:05:26,026 --> 00:05:27,794
We can’t afford
to spend two days

112
00:05:27,828 --> 00:05:28,896
pissing around this place.

113
00:05:28,929 --> 00:05:30,731
Man: So what you’re telling me

114
00:05:30,764 --> 00:05:32,499
is you’d rather let
that baby die?!

115
00:05:32,533 --> 00:05:34,201
( Joseph groans )

116
00:05:34,234 --> 00:05:35,535
Well, I...

117
00:05:35,569 --> 00:05:36,703
Woman: Excuse me.

118
00:05:36,737 --> 00:05:38,606
- I have a suggestion.
- Men: Huh?

119
00:05:38,639 --> 00:05:40,908
Woman: We can kill
two birds with one stone

120
00:05:40,941 --> 00:05:42,042
by having these gentlemen

121
00:05:42,075 --> 00:05:44,644
take him to the doctor
on their way.

122
00:05:44,678 --> 00:05:46,113
Joseph: Uh, nice idea, but--

123
00:05:46,146 --> 00:05:48,515
woman: The cessna
is built to carry four,

124
00:05:48,549 --> 00:05:50,718
but surely there’s
enough room for a baby.

125
00:05:50,751 --> 00:05:52,720
( Kakyoin gasps )

126
00:05:52,753 --> 00:05:55,222
I could have sworn
I just saw it smile

127
00:05:55,255 --> 00:05:58,892
and that the child
already has teeth.

128
00:05:58,926 --> 00:06:00,528
Man: You sure about this, lady?

129
00:06:00,561 --> 00:06:02,797
Do you really want to leave
your baby with these guys?

130
00:06:02,830 --> 00:06:04,899
Joseph: Eh, just a minute.
We can’t do that either.

131
00:06:04,932 --> 00:06:08,169
It’s too dangerous
for the baby to come with us.

132
00:06:08,202 --> 00:06:09,203
( Both sigh )

133
00:06:09,236 --> 00:06:11,105
( Engine sputtering )

134
00:06:14,341 --> 00:06:16,643
Joseph: I told them
this would be dangerous.

135
00:06:16,677 --> 00:06:19,213
Polnareff: Hey, just try
and take it easy, Mr. Joestar.

136
00:06:19,246 --> 00:06:21,782
There’s no way a stand
could catch a plane

137
00:06:21,815 --> 00:06:23,550
flying hundreds
of kilometers an hour.

138
00:06:23,584 --> 00:06:26,720
I mean, we even made sure
the plane itself wasn’t a stand.

139
00:06:26,753 --> 00:06:28,288
I’d say we’re good to go.

140
00:06:28,322 --> 00:06:30,825
Jotaro: I’m far more worried
about the old man’s flying

141
00:06:30,858 --> 00:06:33,194
than I am an attack
from enemy stands.

142
00:06:42,035 --> 00:06:44,838
( Polnareff humming a tune )

143
00:06:48,075 --> 00:06:52,947
Woman: Oh, thank goodness.
What a relief.

144
00:06:52,980 --> 00:06:55,783
By the way, I wonder
who that baby belonged to.

145
00:06:55,816 --> 00:06:57,151
Man: Huh? Are you saying

146
00:06:57,184 --> 00:06:59,253
you’re not the mother
of that child, miss?

147
00:06:59,286 --> 00:07:01,655
Woman: Oh, no. I found it
by the well this morning.

148
00:07:01,688 --> 00:07:04,925
Though, from the moment
I heard the baby’s crying,

149
00:07:04,958 --> 00:07:07,027
I wasn’t able to help myself.

150
00:07:07,060 --> 00:07:09,930
I felt I had to put him
on that plane.

151
00:07:09,963 --> 00:07:12,065
- Man: Ah?
- Man #2: What could happen?

152
00:07:18,772 --> 00:07:20,140
( Polnareff yawns )

153
00:07:21,975 --> 00:07:23,944
( Kakyoin sighs )

154
00:07:23,977 --> 00:07:25,278
Polnareff: Maybe it’s just me,

155
00:07:25,312 --> 00:07:28,649
but I always get so tired
when I get on a plane.

156
00:07:28,682 --> 00:07:30,817
If it’s all right
with you, Mr. Joestar,

157
00:07:30,851 --> 00:07:33,020
I think i’m gonna take
a 30-minute catnap.

158
00:07:33,053 --> 00:07:34,054
Joseph: Sure.

159
00:07:42,329 --> 00:07:44,298
- Polnareff: Huh? Huh?!
- ( Kakyoin gasps )

160
00:07:44,331 --> 00:07:46,667
Polnareff: W-what is this?

161
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:48,936
Hey, kakyoin,
where the hell are we?!

162
00:07:48,969 --> 00:07:50,671
Where’d Mr. Joestar go?!

163
00:07:50,704 --> 00:07:52,072
( Yells )

164
00:07:52,105 --> 00:07:54,808
Kakyoin: This is the same dream
I had this morning,

165
00:07:54,842 --> 00:07:57,178
but now it seems
we’re both inside the dream.

166
00:07:57,211 --> 00:07:58,746
( Polnareff gasps )
What? A dream?

167
00:07:58,779 --> 00:07:59,980
Kakyoin: Yes.

168
00:08:00,013 --> 00:08:01,781
( Polnareff sighs )
That’s a relief.

169
00:08:01,815 --> 00:08:05,185
It’s just a stupid dream.
I was worried for a second,

170
00:08:05,219 --> 00:08:08,789
but if it’s only a dream,
who cares if the dog is dead?

171
00:08:08,822 --> 00:08:11,391
Kakyoin: Polnareff,
you can’t be serious.

172
00:08:11,425 --> 00:08:14,128
Polnareff: Dreams are only
as scary as you make ’em.

173
00:08:14,161 --> 00:08:15,929
That’s kind of the way it goes.

174
00:08:15,963 --> 00:08:17,731
Oh. Just try and relax.

175
00:08:17,764 --> 00:08:20,200
Kakyoin: How can I relax when
we’re having the same dream?!

176
00:08:20,234 --> 00:08:23,070
Polnareff: I suppose
you have a point there.

177
00:08:23,103 --> 00:08:24,805
This is kinda weird.

178
00:08:24,838 --> 00:08:27,274
But in a dream,
isn’t anything possible?

179
00:08:27,307 --> 00:08:29,676
Oh, boy! Would you look at that?

180
00:08:29,710 --> 00:08:31,145
This dreaming thing is great.

181
00:08:31,178 --> 00:08:33,814
So good.

182
00:08:33,847 --> 00:08:36,216
See? All you have to do
to make your dreams fun

183
00:08:36,250 --> 00:08:38,152
is think they’re fun.
( Laughs )

184
00:08:38,185 --> 00:08:40,054
- Kakyoin: Listen.
- ( Polnareff groans )

185
00:08:40,087 --> 00:08:42,256
Kakyoin: Do you remember seeing
the dog’s carcass this morning?

186
00:08:42,289 --> 00:08:44,758
Obviously, the dog and I
had the same dream,

187
00:08:44,791 --> 00:08:47,093
and in that dream, that dog
was unmistakably slaughtered.

188
00:08:47,127 --> 00:08:50,397
Once I was awake,
I found this cut on my hand.

189
00:08:50,430 --> 00:08:52,198
Polnareff: Eh? Where from?

190
00:08:52,232 --> 00:08:55,302
Kakyoin: From the enemy’s stand,
death 13.

191
00:08:55,335 --> 00:08:57,170
Polnareff: The enemy stand?

192
00:08:57,204 --> 00:08:58,806
Kakyoin: Mm-hmm.

193
00:08:58,839 --> 00:09:00,374
Polnareff: Oh, I get it now.

194
00:09:00,407 --> 00:09:02,709
You’re paranoid, ’cause you
had a dream about stands.

195
00:09:02,743 --> 00:09:04,845
Hah! Man, you have
got to take it easy.

196
00:09:04,878 --> 00:09:07,414
Kakyoin: You’re wrong!
It wasn’t a dream about stands.

197
00:09:07,447 --> 00:09:09,015
A stand was in my dream.

198
00:09:09,049 --> 00:09:10,183
Polnareff: That’s what I said.

199
00:09:10,217 --> 00:09:12,319
You were having a dream
about stands.

200
00:09:12,352 --> 00:09:15,322
Kakyoin: Ahh!
You still don’t get it, do you?

201
00:09:15,355 --> 00:09:19,159
Child: Lali-ho! Tell me,
does it hurt being that stupid?

202
00:09:19,193 --> 00:09:20,861
Both: Hmm?

203
00:09:21,995 --> 00:09:23,930
( Polnareff gasps )

204
00:09:23,964 --> 00:09:25,966
Child: Oh, for the love of--

205
00:09:25,999 --> 00:09:27,734
let me spell it out for you!

206
00:09:27,768 --> 00:09:29,970
I’m saying that you’re
slow on the uptake, polnareff!

207
00:09:30,003 --> 00:09:32,372
Polnareff: I-it’s coming
from the dog’s wound.

208
00:09:32,406 --> 00:09:34,742
♪

209
00:09:34,775 --> 00:09:35,743
( Megaphone squeals )

210
00:09:35,776 --> 00:09:37,011
Child: Lali-ho!

211
00:09:37,044 --> 00:09:38,946
Allow me to welcome you
to my humble abode.

212
00:09:38,979 --> 00:09:41,482
This is a dream,
and i’m the grim reaper!

213
00:09:41,515 --> 00:09:42,916
Polnareff: It’s a megaphone?

214
00:09:44,518 --> 00:09:46,553
♪

215
00:09:50,791 --> 00:09:53,027
What the--what is that thing?!

216
00:09:53,060 --> 00:09:54,461
Kakyoin: Polnareff,
stay on guard,

217
00:09:54,495 --> 00:09:57,131
and watch closely.
That fiend is death 13.

218
00:09:58,365 --> 00:10:00,367
( Polnareff gasping )

219
00:10:02,436 --> 00:10:04,838
W-w...

220
00:10:04,872 --> 00:10:07,308
( Screams )

221
00:10:07,341 --> 00:10:10,077
Kakyoin: Come forth,
hierophant green!

222
00:10:10,110 --> 00:10:11,778
( Polnareff gags )

223
00:10:11,812 --> 00:10:13,981
Kakyoin: Hierophant, attack!

224
00:10:14,014 --> 00:10:15,382
( Polnareff gags ) Chario--

225
00:10:17,518 --> 00:10:19,420
kakyoin: Why can’t I
summon hierophant?

226
00:10:19,453 --> 00:10:20,888
What is this?

227
00:10:20,921 --> 00:10:23,891
Polnareff: Chariot is
not coming out either.

228
00:10:23,924 --> 00:10:27,027
Kakyoin: Is it because we’re
in some kind of twisted dream?

229
00:10:27,060 --> 00:10:28,528
Death 13: Lali-ho!

230
00:10:28,562 --> 00:10:30,564
It’s romantic,
wouldn’t you agree,

231
00:10:30,597 --> 00:10:33,033
being able to die in a dream?

232
00:10:33,066 --> 00:10:35,569
Lali-ho.

233
00:10:40,107 --> 00:10:41,675
( Polnareff groans )

234
00:10:41,708 --> 00:10:43,476
( Kakyoin moans )

235
00:10:45,779 --> 00:10:48,448
Joseph: Eh, jotaro,
do you sense that?

236
00:10:48,482 --> 00:10:51,085
Jotaro: Yeah, clear as day.

237
00:10:51,118 --> 00:10:53,554
( Polnareff gagging )

238
00:10:57,624 --> 00:10:59,526
Death 13: Are you stupid?

239
00:10:59,560 --> 00:11:03,364
Surely you know by now that only
a stand can defeat a stand.

240
00:11:03,397 --> 00:11:07,968
It’s time for you to enter
your eternal sleep, polnareff.

241
00:11:09,002 --> 00:11:10,770
Lali-ho.

242
00:11:10,804 --> 00:11:11,772
Kakyoin: Polnareff!

243
00:11:11,805 --> 00:11:13,473
Death 13: Die!

244
00:11:13,507 --> 00:11:14,608
Huh?

245
00:11:16,977 --> 00:11:20,047
- ( Polnareff gasping )
- Joseph: Polnareff.

246
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:22,950
Hey, polnareff, wake up.

247
00:11:22,983 --> 00:11:26,019
It would appear our little
traveler has wet himself.

248
00:11:26,053 --> 00:11:28,389
Do us all a favor,
and change his diaper.

249
00:11:28,422 --> 00:11:29,857
Polnareff: Huh? ( Scoffs )

250
00:11:29,890 --> 00:11:31,792
- Jotaro: Hmm?
- ( Baby mutters )

251
00:11:31,825 --> 00:11:33,627
Death 13: Eh, curses.

252
00:11:33,660 --> 00:11:36,763
Someone must have woken
the fool from his slumber.

253
00:11:36,797 --> 00:11:39,099
He’s quite lucky.

254
00:11:39,132 --> 00:11:40,100
( Kakyoin shudders )

255
00:11:40,133 --> 00:11:41,167
Death 13: Lali-ho.

256
00:11:41,201 --> 00:11:42,936
I suppose it’s no matter.

257
00:11:42,970 --> 00:11:46,574
Even if he wakes up, he won’t
remember a single thing.

258
00:11:46,607 --> 00:11:49,944
I’ll just have to finish him
the next time he falls asleep.

259
00:11:49,977 --> 00:11:54,048
Which means your death
has been moved up.

260
00:11:55,082 --> 00:11:56,850
Lali-ho!

261
00:11:56,884 --> 00:11:59,720
Joseph: Hey, there, polnareff,
have you woken up yet?

262
00:11:59,753 --> 00:12:01,855
I’d like that diaper changed
this year.

263
00:12:01,889 --> 00:12:03,858
Polnareff: All right.
I’m up. I’m up.

264
00:12:03,891 --> 00:12:06,193
( Sighs ) Man...

265
00:12:06,226 --> 00:12:09,463
I feel like I had some
kind of terrifying nightmare,

266
00:12:09,496 --> 00:12:12,666
but i--i don’t remember
what happened at all.

267
00:12:12,699 --> 00:12:14,634
I’ve completely forgotten.

268
00:12:14,668 --> 00:12:16,436
Joseph: After you change
the boy’s diaper,

269
00:12:16,470 --> 00:12:19,506
you can head back to dreamland
to finish your business.

270
00:12:19,540 --> 00:12:20,908
I won’t wake you up again.

271
00:12:20,941 --> 00:12:22,910
( Kakyoin shuddering )

272
00:12:22,943 --> 00:12:25,212
( Polnareff gags )

273
00:12:25,245 --> 00:12:27,080
Merde! Hold on a second, guys.

274
00:12:27,114 --> 00:12:28,682
What the hell is this?!

275
00:12:28,715 --> 00:12:31,017
The kid took a dump
in his diaper.

276
00:12:31,051 --> 00:12:33,086
Just look at the size of it.

277
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:34,855
Joseph: Well,
he is a baby, you know.

278
00:12:34,888 --> 00:12:36,523
That’s why he wears diapers.

279
00:12:36,557 --> 00:12:38,692
Polnareff: You’re kidding me!
That’s why?!

280
00:12:39,993 --> 00:12:41,495
C’est degueulasse.

281
00:12:41,528 --> 00:12:42,863
What a vile,
disgusting creature.

282
00:12:42,896 --> 00:12:45,198
And he’s gotten it
all over the place!

283
00:12:45,232 --> 00:12:46,767
Joseph: Would you stop yapping

284
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:49,503
and change the damn diaper
already? It stinks.

285
00:12:49,536 --> 00:12:50,937
( Polnareff sighs )

286
00:12:50,971 --> 00:12:53,507
How are you not embarrassed?

287
00:12:53,540 --> 00:12:56,910
Do us all a favor,
and grow up already.

288
00:12:56,944 --> 00:13:00,114
Does this look right to you?

289
00:13:00,147 --> 00:13:01,715
Well, it looks good to me.

290
00:13:01,748 --> 00:13:04,251
Jotaro, I need you
to hold on to the edge there.

291
00:13:04,284 --> 00:13:05,685
I’m gonna try and pin it.

292
00:13:05,719 --> 00:13:07,688
Jotaro: Okay. Like this?

293
00:13:07,721 --> 00:13:11,725
Polnareff: Yeah, I think so.
Now hold on to the baby.

294
00:13:11,758 --> 00:13:14,127
( Kakyoin shuddering )

295
00:13:17,764 --> 00:13:19,733
( Murmuring )

296
00:13:19,766 --> 00:13:21,001
Both: Hmm?

297
00:13:21,034 --> 00:13:22,102
( Kakyoin groans )

298
00:13:22,135 --> 00:13:24,070
Death 13: Lali-ho!

299
00:13:24,104 --> 00:13:26,807
( Kakyoin screams )
Stop it! Stop it!

300
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:29,009
- Jotaro: Kakyoin, what’s wrong?
- Polnareff: Hey!

301
00:13:29,042 --> 00:13:30,510
Joseph: What’s going on?

302
00:13:30,544 --> 00:13:33,547
Kakyoin: Stop it! Stop it!
Stop it! Stop!

303
00:13:33,580 --> 00:13:35,515
( Joseph yells )

304
00:13:35,549 --> 00:13:36,717
Damn it!

305
00:13:38,752 --> 00:13:40,754
I’ve lost control!

306
00:13:40,787 --> 00:13:43,723
Jotaro: Wait. Are you saying
that we’re gonna crash?

307
00:13:43,757 --> 00:13:45,525
- Kakyoin: Stop!
- Polnareff: Kakyoin,

308
00:13:45,559 --> 00:13:47,227
what’s the matter with you?

309
00:13:47,261 --> 00:13:49,764
He’s been this way
since he woke up!

310
00:13:49,796 --> 00:13:51,998
Joseph: I don’t care.
Just calm him down.

311
00:13:52,032 --> 00:13:55,002
Jotaro: Old man, if you don’t
regain control of this thing,

312
00:13:55,035 --> 00:13:56,036
we’re all done for.

313
00:13:59,573 --> 00:14:02,943
Death 13: Kakyoin, you need to
pull yourself together, pronto.

314
00:14:02,976 --> 00:14:05,579
We’re about to crash
because of you.

315
00:14:05,612 --> 00:14:07,981
Lali-ho.

316
00:14:08,015 --> 00:14:09,783
Talk about a restless sleeper.

317
00:14:09,816 --> 00:14:11,284
At this rate,
you’ll kill us both,

318
00:14:11,318 --> 00:14:13,587
you and my user, that is.

319
00:14:13,620 --> 00:14:15,555
Kakyoin: Y-your user
is that baby?

320
00:14:15,589 --> 00:14:17,825
How in the world
is that possible?

321
00:14:19,059 --> 00:14:20,227
No way.

322
00:14:20,260 --> 00:14:23,130
He’s only about six months old.

323
00:14:23,163 --> 00:14:26,733
Death 13: Wrong. I’m 11 months,
almost a year old.

324
00:14:26,767 --> 00:14:29,203
It may also interest you
to know that i’m a genius.

325
00:14:29,236 --> 00:14:31,004
I may poop in my diapers,

326
00:14:31,038 --> 00:14:34,141
but I know a hell of a lot more
than you fools!

327
00:14:34,174 --> 00:14:38,178
Lali-ho-ho-ho-ho-ho.

328
00:14:39,346 --> 00:14:42,316
( Kakyoin screams )

329
00:14:42,349 --> 00:14:45,118
( Gagging )

330
00:14:49,189 --> 00:14:53,093
Death 13: And with that, you’ve
lost your ability to scream.

331
00:14:53,126 --> 00:14:54,260
( Laughs )

332
00:14:54,294 --> 00:14:56,163
Kakyoin: A stand within a dream.

333
00:14:56,196 --> 00:15:00,333
I have to find a way to let
Mr. Joestar and jotaro know.

334
00:15:03,003 --> 00:15:03,971
Death 13: Hmm?

335
00:15:04,004 --> 00:15:05,272
Polnareff: What are you doing?

336
00:15:05,305 --> 00:15:06,840
- Mr. Joestar!
- Jotaro: Damn it. Level us out.

337
00:15:06,874 --> 00:15:08,075
Joseph: Just calm down.

338
00:15:08,108 --> 00:15:09,276
Can’t you see
i’m working on that

339
00:15:09,309 --> 00:15:11,912
while trying
to stay cool and collected?

340
00:15:13,280 --> 00:15:14,915
Kakyoin: I’m not waking up.

341
00:15:14,948 --> 00:15:16,216
Death 13: Lali-ho.

342
00:15:16,250 --> 00:15:18,352
Looks to me
like no one’s going to notice

343
00:15:18,385 --> 00:15:19,887
if you’re cutting your arm

344
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:21,822
with a knife
that’s smaller than my wee-wee.

345
00:15:21,855 --> 00:15:26,126
Besides, you can hurt yourself
all you want in this dream,

346
00:15:26,159 --> 00:15:27,927
but it won’t wake you up.

347
00:15:27,961 --> 00:15:31,031
As long as you’re asleep,
I completely control

348
00:15:31,064 --> 00:15:34,034
every iota
of your precious mind.

349
00:15:34,067 --> 00:15:36,102
My stand, death 13,

350
00:15:36,136 --> 00:15:38,639
infiltrates the minds
of its slumbering victims

351
00:15:38,672 --> 00:15:40,941
when they are
at their most vulnerable.

352
00:15:42,309 --> 00:15:44,778
Kakyoin: Damn it. Stop.

353
00:15:47,447 --> 00:15:48,682
( Joseph screaming )

354
00:15:48,715 --> 00:15:50,016
Jotaro: What’s wrong, old man?

355
00:15:50,050 --> 00:15:52,419
We’re crashing.

356
00:15:52,452 --> 00:15:55,021
Joseph: I’ll control it
with hermit purple.

357
00:15:59,193 --> 00:16:00,795
- I did it!
- Polnareff: Whoo-hoo!

358
00:16:00,827 --> 00:16:03,163
Joseph: I lifted the plane
just in the Nick of time!

359
00:16:03,197 --> 00:16:04,932
Polnareff: What a close one.

360
00:16:04,965 --> 00:16:06,366
( Baby sighs )

361
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:09,837
Death 13: It would seem
we managed to avoid crashing.

362
00:16:09,870 --> 00:16:11,972
That was too close for comfort.

363
00:16:12,005 --> 00:16:14,941
Now, then, what do you say

364
00:16:14,975 --> 00:16:17,845
to me killing you
by crushing that heart of yours?

365
00:16:17,878 --> 00:16:19,380
That way, joestar and the others

366
00:16:19,413 --> 00:16:21,148
will think
you had a heart attack

367
00:16:21,181 --> 00:16:23,183
and died of natural causes.

368
00:16:23,217 --> 00:16:24,185
( Kakyoin grunting )

369
00:16:24,218 --> 00:16:26,787
Death 13: Die, kakyoin.

370
00:16:26,820 --> 00:16:28,322
Joseph: Did you guys see that?

371
00:16:28,355 --> 00:16:30,257
How do you boys
like them apples?

372
00:16:30,290 --> 00:16:32,425
- My flying’s not too shabby.
- Polnareff: Well done.

373
00:16:32,459 --> 00:16:33,894
- Jotaro: Hey.
- Joseph: Hmm?

374
00:16:33,927 --> 00:16:35,061
( Men yell )

375
00:16:37,097 --> 00:16:38,465
Joseph: What? Why the hell

376
00:16:38,499 --> 00:16:41,736
is there a palm tree
all the way out here?

377
00:16:41,768 --> 00:16:43,403
Jotaro: Good grief. Damn.

378
00:16:44,471 --> 00:16:46,306
I knew you’d do this.

379
00:16:46,340 --> 00:16:47,441
( Kakyoin gasps )

380
00:16:52,779 --> 00:16:54,781
( Insects chirping )

381
00:16:57,918 --> 00:16:59,787
Joseph: Hmm.

382
00:17:04,291 --> 00:17:06,827
Polnareff: Is this enough,
Mr. Joestar?

383
00:17:06,860 --> 00:17:08,895
Joseph: Yeah. Thank you.

384
00:17:08,929 --> 00:17:10,164
( Polnareff sighs )

385
00:17:10,197 --> 00:17:12,132
We survived, but...

386
00:17:12,166 --> 00:17:14,969
Kakyoin, what’s going on, man?

387
00:17:15,002 --> 00:17:18,172
This is all your fault,
you know?

388
00:17:18,205 --> 00:17:20,140
Kakyoin: I’m not sure.

389
00:17:20,174 --> 00:17:23,477
I feel like I just endured
a horrible dream,

390
00:17:23,510 --> 00:17:26,747
and when I awoke,
I was utterly exhausted.

391
00:17:26,780 --> 00:17:29,950
I think there’s
something wrong with me.

392
00:17:29,983 --> 00:17:33,220
Joseph: Try and cheer up.
It’s probably a case of fatigue.

393
00:17:33,253 --> 00:17:36,323
It’s been about a month now
since we left Japan,

394
00:17:36,356 --> 00:17:38,859
and the enemy’s
been attacking us nonstop

395
00:17:38,892 --> 00:17:40,193
ever since that day.

396
00:17:40,227 --> 00:17:41,962
Jotaro: Hey.

397
00:17:41,995 --> 00:17:44,798
It looks like the baby’s fever
has finally gone down.

398
00:17:44,832 --> 00:17:46,500
Joseph: Thank goodness
he’s safe and sound.

399
00:17:46,533 --> 00:17:49,136
If anything were to happen,
to this little guy,

400
00:17:49,169 --> 00:17:50,270
i’d never forgive myself.

401
00:17:50,304 --> 00:17:53,107
( Laughs )

402
00:17:53,140 --> 00:17:55,909
Peek-a-boo. Bleh!

403
00:17:55,943 --> 00:17:57,111
( Baby laughs )

404
00:17:57,144 --> 00:17:59,113
Joseph: Peek-a-boo. Bleh.

405
00:17:59,146 --> 00:18:00,314
( Baby laughs )

406
00:18:00,347 --> 00:18:02,282
Joseph: He has
such an adorable smile,

407
00:18:02,316 --> 00:18:03,951
don’t you think?

408
00:18:03,984 --> 00:18:05,452
Polnareff: I really
don’t get what’s so funny.

409
00:18:05,485 --> 00:18:07,420
You’re not even
making any jokes,

410
00:18:07,454 --> 00:18:09,923
just faces. What an idiot.

411
00:18:09,957 --> 00:18:11,058
♪

412
00:18:11,091 --> 00:18:13,160
Baby: Oh, put a sock in it.

413
00:18:13,193 --> 00:18:16,329
This isn’t my idea
of a perfect night, either.

414
00:18:16,363 --> 00:18:18,932
Jotaro: Hey, old man,
the radio survived.

415
00:18:18,966 --> 00:18:20,201
What should we do?

416
00:18:20,234 --> 00:18:22,937
Should we send out an s.O.S?

417
00:18:22,970 --> 00:18:25,172
That’ll mean dio
can find us, but...

418
00:18:25,205 --> 00:18:26,807
Joseph: We have to.

419
00:18:26,840 --> 00:18:29,409
Let’s call for a rescue,
for the baby’s sake.

420
00:18:29,443 --> 00:18:30,411
( Baby coos )

421
00:18:30,444 --> 00:18:32,846
( Kakyoin sighs )

422
00:18:32,880 --> 00:18:34,181
Huh?

423
00:18:34,214 --> 00:18:36,917
I thought I was feeling
twinges of pain.

424
00:18:36,950 --> 00:18:38,452
I’m bleeding.

425
00:18:38,485 --> 00:18:41,455
Wait. Did I cut it
when we crashed?

426
00:18:42,890 --> 00:18:43,958
( Gasps )

427
00:18:43,991 --> 00:18:45,960
♪

428
00:18:47,361 --> 00:18:48,362
( Gasps )

429
00:18:50,163 --> 00:18:53,066
What’s this?
The cuts form letters.

430
00:18:53,100 --> 00:18:54,868
"Baby...stand"?

431
00:18:54,902 --> 00:18:56,470
But how did they--

432
00:18:56,503 --> 00:18:58,105
I don’t know what it means,

433
00:18:58,138 --> 00:18:59,940
even though it’s my handwriting.

434
00:18:59,973 --> 00:19:02,075
I can’t remember anything.

435
00:19:02,109 --> 00:19:05,412
Did I do this to myself?

436
00:19:07,347 --> 00:19:09,516
There isn’t any blood
on my knife,

437
00:19:09,550 --> 00:19:12,920
but it seems the cuts
were made with this blade.

438
00:19:12,953 --> 00:19:14,488
How strange.

439
00:19:14,521 --> 00:19:18,258
Could I have really forgotten
violently cutting my own arm?

440
00:19:21,161 --> 00:19:25,599
Baby: Damn it. I was told
that they were a clever bunch,

441
00:19:25,632 --> 00:19:29,102
but this one actually carved
letters into his arm

442
00:19:29,136 --> 00:19:31,071
while he was cutting himself.

443
00:19:31,104 --> 00:19:32,505
- ( Groans )
- Kakyoin: Hmm?

444
00:19:32,539 --> 00:19:34,508
( Baby gasps )

445
00:19:34,541 --> 00:19:38,245
Kakyoin: What was that look
on the baby’s face just now?

446
00:19:38,278 --> 00:19:40,514
It’s as if he
deliberately looked away

447
00:19:40,547 --> 00:19:42,082
the moment I met his gaze.

448
00:19:42,115 --> 00:19:43,116
( Gasps )

449
00:19:45,152 --> 00:19:46,520
Baby...

450
00:19:46,553 --> 00:19:48,922
Stand.

451
00:19:48,956 --> 00:19:50,624
- ( Gasps )
- ( Baby groans )

452
00:19:52,059 --> 00:19:55,663
Baby stand.

453
00:20:01,101 --> 00:20:05,339
I hate to say it, but I might
be losing my mind, because...

454
00:20:07,174 --> 00:20:10,244
I’m starting to think...

455
00:20:10,277 --> 00:20:11,478
( Baby yelps )

456
00:20:11,512 --> 00:20:13,647
Kakyoin: That this baby
is a stand user!

457
00:20:13,680 --> 00:20:15,048
( Baby crying )

458
00:20:16,083 --> 00:20:17,351
Joseph: Hey, kakyoin,

459
00:20:17,384 --> 00:20:19,353
what do you think you’re doing?

460
00:20:19,386 --> 00:20:21,054
( Baby crying )

461
00:20:21,088 --> 00:20:23,357
Joseph: Come on, now.
That is way too rough.

462
00:20:23,390 --> 00:20:26,526
You could strangle the boy.
What’s wrong with you?

463
00:20:26,560 --> 00:20:27,961
Kakyoin: My apologies.

464
00:20:27,995 --> 00:20:29,263
Joseph: There, there.

465
00:20:29,296 --> 00:20:31,131
Everything’s all right.

466
00:20:31,165 --> 00:20:33,300
Joseph: Let’s have
something to eat, shall we?

467
00:20:33,333 --> 00:20:37,037
He should calm down
once he has some food in him.

468
00:20:37,070 --> 00:20:40,206
Polnareff: Hey, jotaro,
it looks like poor kakyoin’s

469
00:20:40,240 --> 00:20:42,476
really starting
to lose it out here.

470
00:20:42,509 --> 00:20:43,643
Jotaro: Hmm.

471
00:20:43,677 --> 00:20:45,045
Joseph: There, there...

472
00:20:45,078 --> 00:20:46,379
Polnareff: I wonder
if he’ll make it

473
00:20:46,413 --> 00:20:48,048
through the rest of this trip.

474
00:20:49,683 --> 00:20:51,451
♪

475
00:21:01,228 --> 00:21:03,263
( Baby laughs )

476
00:21:05,699 --> 00:21:07,701
♪

477
00:21:19,546 --> 00:21:22,015
♪ All the old paintings
on the tomb ♪

478
00:21:22,049 --> 00:21:24,285
♪ they do the sand dance,
don’t you know ♪

479
00:21:24,318 --> 00:21:25,419
♪ if they move too quick

480
00:21:25,452 --> 00:21:26,987
♪ oh, whey, oh

481
00:21:27,020 --> 00:21:28,755
♪ they’re falling down
like a domino ♪

482
00:21:28,789 --> 00:21:31,292
♪ all the bazaar men
by the nile ♪

483
00:21:31,325 --> 00:21:33,394
♪ they got the money on a bet

484
00:21:33,427 --> 00:21:34,595
♪ gold crocodiles

485
00:21:34,628 --> 00:21:36,130
♪ oh, whey, oh

486
00:21:36,163 --> 00:21:38,198
♪ they snap their teeth
on your cigarette ♪

487
00:21:38,232 --> 00:21:40,334
♪ foreign types
with the hookah pipes say ♪

488
00:21:40,367 --> 00:21:42,603
♪ whey, oh, whey, oh

489
00:21:42,636 --> 00:21:46,340
♪ ay, whey, oh, whey, oh

490
00:21:47,441 --> 00:21:50,077
♪ walk like an Egyptian

491
00:22:01,321 --> 00:22:04,024
♪ The blond waitresses
take their trays ♪

492
00:22:04,057 --> 00:22:06,126
♪ they spin around,
and they cross the floor ♪

493
00:22:06,159 --> 00:22:07,394
♪ they’ve got the moves

494
00:22:07,427 --> 00:22:08,395
♪ oh, whey, oh

495
00:22:08,428 --> 00:22:09,429
♪ you drop your drink

496
00:22:09,463 --> 00:22:10,731
♪ then they bring you more

497
00:22:10,764 --> 00:22:13,200
♪ all the school kids
so sick of books ♪

498
00:22:13,233 --> 00:22:15,402
♪ they like the punk
and the metal band ♪

499
00:22:15,435 --> 00:22:16,636
♪ when the buzzer rings

500
00:22:16,670 --> 00:22:18,138
